---
// Compact Oregon-in-national-context teaser. The "map fragment" is a stylized
// SVG block diagram of the Pacific Northwest with Oregon highlighted, not a
// real cartographic projection — this is a teaser, not a state tracker.
---
<section class="bg-oastl-bone border-y border-oastl-forest/15">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-12 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-[1fr_1.4fr] items-center">
    <figure class="border border-oastl-forest/20 bg-oastl-cream/40 rounded-sm p-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 200 130" class="w-full h-auto" role="img" aria-label="Map fragment with Oregon highlighted among the 20 trust-lands states">
        <!-- Stylized states block: greyed neighbors with Oregon picked out -->
        <rect x="10" y="20"  width="55" height="40" fill="#f5f1e8" stroke="#5f6c80" stroke-width="0.8" />
        <rect x="65" y="20"  width="50" height="40" fill="#f5f1e8" stroke="#5f6c80" stroke-width="0.8" />
        <rect x="115" y="20" width="75" height="40" fill="#f5f1e8" stroke="#5f6c80" stroke-width="0.8" />
        <!-- Oregon (highlight) -->
        <rect x="10" y="60"  width="55" height="40" fill="#1b3252" stroke="#0e1b2e" stroke-width="1.2" />
        <text x="37.5" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-family="IBM Plex Mono, monospace" font-size="9" fill="#f5f1e8" letter-spacing="2">OR</text>
        <!-- neighbors -->
        <rect x="65" y="60"  width="50" height="40" fill="#f5f1e8" stroke="#5f6c80" stroke-width="0.8" />
        <rect x="115" y="60" width="75" height="40" fill="#f5f1e8" stroke="#5f6c80" stroke-width="0.8" />
        <!-- status dot -->
        <circle cx="58" cy="68" r="3" fill="#a87f2c" />
      </svg>
      <figcaption class="mt-3 text-xs text-oastl-ink/60 font-mono uppercase tracking-wide text-center">
        Oregon · Active litigation · Reform pending
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-oastl-forest mb-2">Oregon in the national context</div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-oastl-ink font-semibold leading-tight">
        One of twenty trust-lands states. The one with active appellate precedent.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-oastl-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
        Twenty states received federal school-trust grants at admission. Each manages its trust differently; only a few have ever faced beneficiary-led enforcement litigation. Oregon’s January 2026 appellate victory is the precedent the other nineteen will be watching.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://schooltrustlands.net/state-tracker/"
        class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-oastl-action font-medium hover:text-oastl-gold"
      >
        See the national picture at ASTL’s State Tracker →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
